                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus from="48r" facs="052">Fols 48r and following</locus><title>Image of John, Son of Thunder, Mälk‘a Yoḥannǝs Wäldä Nägwädǝgwad, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልክአ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡</foreign></title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.1"><locus from="40r" facs="044">Fols 40r and following</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer"> Asmat Prayer on John 1:1–4 as protection against demons and evil people and sorcerers</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.2"><locus from="40v" to="48r" facs="045">Fols 40v–48r</locus><title>Image of John, Son of Thunder, Mälk‘a Yoḥannǝs Wäldä Nägwädǝgwad, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልክአ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡</foreign></title><incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ መግረሬ፡ ፀር፡ ወመፍትሔ፡ ሀብት፡ ዘነገሮ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡ እንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ በገነት፡ ከመ፡ ይዕቀብ፡ ሥጋሃ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ያሮክ፡ ያሮክ፡ ያሮክ፡ ከምላድ፡ ከላዩድ፡ ህልክናድ፡ ሲምኑድ፡ በቃለ፡ እሉ፡ አስማት፡ ሀበኒ፡ ሀብተ፡ ወሢመተ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>combined with the first line from six of the sections of Psalm 118 (each of which begins with a successive Hebrew letter): mem, gimal, zyin samech, vav, and taph and are combined with an asmat prayer as protection from an enemy and for gaining wealth</note>
                </msItem>
