                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1030Trinity">The Trinity</ref> surrounded by the Four Living Creatures</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#3r" facs="007">Fol. 3r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3417David">David</persName> and Solomon, based on the text of the image</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#5r" facs="009">Fol. 5r</locus><desc>The four heads of Qerubim, based on the text of the image</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#5v" facs="010">Fol. 5v</locus><desc>Unknown (a winged creature standing between two plants with red flowers)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#6r" facs="010">Fol. 6r</locus><desc>Four serpents. Prayer “Save me and protect me from the evil ones whose mouth is like the serpent. . . .”</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#6v" facs="011">Fol. 6v</locus><desc>Box with X-shape creating four triangular spaces, each with a <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> asmat prayer, e.g., “Put fear inside the heart of my enemies. . . “ (top)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#8v" facs="013">Fol. 8v</locus><desc> Lamb holding <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1071Cross">Cross</ref> with caption (reading from inside to outside): <q>“Behold, the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world, Alpha and O[mega], Beta, Iota, Ahǝya òärahya, Jesus Christ, son of God, Victor and Son of Mary, the Virgin, protect me suffering and perdition, your servant, Ḫaylä Maryam.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#11r" facs="015">Fol. 11r</locus><desc>Box with X-shape creating four triangular spaces, each with a <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> asmat prayer, e.g., “Look upon my prayer for your servant” (top);  “Rebuke my enemies and adversaries” (bottom)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#11v" facs="016">Fol. 11v</locus><desc>Two Serpents. <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> Asmat prayer written in a circular flow in the center (from the inside): “Give me deliverance from spear and sword. . . .”</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#22r" facs="026">Fol. 22r</locus><desc>Four Serpents:  <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> Asmat prayer written in a circular flow in the center (from the inside): “Save me and protect me from the hand of the children of aliens who prepare their mouths as the mouths of serpents.  They stretch their bow to do harm.”</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#22v" facs="027">Fol. 22v</locus><desc>Four <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref>s in the corners around a box with an X shape.  <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> Four texts are at top, bottom, right and left, e.g., bottom: “Rebuke my enemies and adversaries.  With this asmat, protect me, your servant Ḫaylä Maryam.”</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#25r" facs="029">Fol. 25r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13"><locus target="#26r" facs="030">Fol. 26r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8065Raguel">Raguel</persName>, here called “steward of lights,” with wings outstretched, holding sun and moon</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14"><locus target="#27r" facs="031">Fol. 27r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d15"><locus target="#31r" facs="035"> f. 31r, upper margin</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref><persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d16"><locus target="#32r" facs="036">Fol. 32r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName>, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d17"><locus target="#33r" facs="037">Fol. 33r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10930Rufael">Rufāʾel</persName>, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d18"><locus target="#34r" facs="038">Fol. 34r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8065Raguel">Raguel</persName>, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d19"><locus target="#35r" facs="039">Fol. 35r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> Saquel, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d20"><locus target="#36r" facs="040">Fol. 36r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7840Phanuel">Phanuel</persName>, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d21"><locus target="#37r" facs="041">Fol. 37r</locus><desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> Afnin, with wings outstretched</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d22"><locus target="#38v" facs="043">Fol. 38v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with caption <q>“Mary, daughter of Hanna and Joakim, rainbow of Patriarch Shem, intercede for your beloved son, Savior of the World.  May He visit me from heaven. Your servant and sinner, Ḫaylä Maryam. Amen.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d23"><locus target="#39v" facs="044">Fol. 39v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>John, Son of Thunder</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d24"><locus target="#44r" facs="048">Fol. 44r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref> with caption (l. to r.): <q>“He said to his mother, ‘behold, your son.’” “He said to his disciple, ‘behold, your mother.’”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d25"><locus target="#46r" facs="050">Fol. 46r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10245Yared">Yāred</persName> and Saint John. With caption <q>“How Saint Yarәd, the Singer, praised Saint John, the Evangelist.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d26">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #7r #12r #23r #26v #29v #40r #52v" facs="005 011 016 027 031 034 044 057">folss. 1r, 7r, 12r, 23r, 26v, 29v, 40r, 52v, </locus> (ornate, colorful ḫarägs);
                    <locus target="#30v #47v #50r #57r" facs="035 052 054 061">30v, 47v, 50r, 57r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
